    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-05-20T18:21:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-05-20T18:21:00-05:00" n="291"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">886A.2553/5–2053: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 291<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Saudi Arabia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d291fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_FAD1"
                            >Fritzlan</persName> and cleared by <gloss target="#t_NE1">NE</gloss>
                        and <gloss target="#t_PED1">PED</gloss>. Repeated as telegram 252 to
                        Dhahran.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-05-20T19:21:00-04:00"
                            >May 20, 1953—7:21 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>646. Department informed by <gloss target="#t_Aramco1">Aramco</gloss> that as
                    result recent price fixing negotiations <gloss target="#t_Aramco1"
                        >Aramco</gloss> confronted by Saudi proposal that new values (1.462 for Ras
                    Tanura 1.898 for Saudi-Jordan frontier) be accepted for future and made
                    retroactive to cover period from beginning 1951 and be basis of sharing earnings
                    for this period. <gloss target="#t_Aramco1">Aramco</gloss> negotiators had
                    indicated this not acceptable but they would be willing recommend price increase
                    be made retroactive to beginning 1952.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Aramco1">Aramco</gloss> has now received report from <persName
                        corresp="#p_DFA1">Davies</persName> stating negotiations to be resumed May
                    21 under chairmanship <persName corresp="#p_IAAF1">Faisal</persName> and that
                    according reliable but unofficial information Saudi proposals to be presented as
                    having approval of King and constituting last word. If <gloss
                        target="#t_Aramco1">Aramco</gloss> reaction negative Saudis reportedly
                    prepared “take steps protect their interest”, presumably implying immediate
                    retaliatory measures and possibly eventual nationalization.</p>
                <p>In face of such ultimatum <gloss target="#t_Aramco1">Aramco</gloss> negotiators
                    have been authorized accept Saudi proposals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SGW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
